.NH 4
.XN -N AAAU -- Subroutine \fCcgca_inithead\fP
.PP
This routine is used to initialise the list, i.e. create
the first node.
.DS L
.CW
subroutine cgca_inithead( head, payload )
type( cgca_lnklst_node ), pointer, intent( out ) :: head
type( cgca_lnklst_tpayld ), intent( in ) :: payload
.DE
.PP
The routine allocates memory for one node,
sets its
.CW value
to
.CW payload
and returns the pointer to this node in
.CW head .
The node's
.CW next
is set to
.CW NULL ,
i.e. the pointer is not associated:
.DS L
.CW
allocate( head )
head%value = payload
head%next => null()
.DE
.PP
After calling this routine the linked list will look
like this:
.PS 0.8i
copy "lnklst2.pic"
.PE
